  <h1>School API Documentation</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>1. GET /listSchools/:latitude/:longitude</h2>
    <p>Returns a list of schools sorted by proximity to the given geographic coordinates.</p>
    <p><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>latitude</code> - User's latitude (decimal degrees)</li>
      <li><code>longitude</code> - User's longitude (decimal degrees)</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>
    <pre>GET /listSchools/28.6139/77.2090</pre>
    <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>
    <pre>[
  {
    "schoolName": "Sunrise Valley High",
    "schoolDistance": 4
  },
  {
    "schoolName": "Greenwood Public School",
    "schoolDistance": 13
  }
]</pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. POST /addSchool</h2>
    <p>Adds a new school to the database.</p>
    <p><strong>Example Request body:</strong></p>
    <pre>{
  "name": "Greenwood Public School",
  "address": "Sector 9, Rohini, Delhi",
  "latitude": 28.7166,
  "longitude": 77.1395
}</pre>
    <p><strong>Response:</strong> Confirmation with inserted school details or validation error.</p>
  </section>

